HEADWORD: Sacristan
<hw>Sac"ris*tan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sacristain</ets>, LL. <ets>sacrista</ets>, fr. L. <ets>sacer</ets>.
See <er>Sacred</er>, and cf. <er>Sexton</er>.]</ety> <def>An officer of
the church who has the care of the utensils or movables, and of the
church in general; a sexton.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

